    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3267b432_1e20b797",
        "filename": "src/images/SkJpegEncoder.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-01T14:58:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m leaning towards not.  We could have a base class with a virtual onEncodeRows() that was overridden by Jpeg and Png.  I believe that Webp cannot and does not need to support row-by-row encoding.\n\nEverything else is very format specific.  And all of the current callsites seem to use a switch statement anyway to select the Skia format enum.  I think it\u0027s nice for the three implementations to be totally separate.",
      "parentUuid": "57c823b4_b2fbfbf6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "3adbc4e8f7ccf31da575ae74f11df7f4e89fd46e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f8a05976_17df02ed",
        "filename": "src/images/SkJpegEncoder.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-01T13:40:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we don\u0027t support doing something with the alpha channel, are there other (future) reasons to have an Options struct, rather than a single int?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "3adbc4e8f7ccf31da575ae74f11df7f4e89fd46e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "09632756_a7d17960",
        "filename": "src/images/SkJpegEncoder.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-01T14:58:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think so.  There are seemingly endless encoding options.  I\u0027m just adding them as we need them.  A non-complete list of things that we might want later:\n(1) Control how the Huffman tables are created.\n(2) Arithmetic vs Huffman encoding\n(3) That perceptual encoding idea?\n\nAnd I will definitely *need* to add the alpha options in order to support Chrome.",
      "parentUuid": "f8a05976_17df02ed",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "3adbc4e8f7ccf31da575ae74f11df7f4e89fd46e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
