      "writtenOn": "2017-05-01T13:40:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It seems weird to me that this will only return false due to a dumb client. (i.e. client passed a bad value or keeps calling after the encode is complete)\n\nMaybe there\u0027s no need to return a boolean? What will the call site look like? It kind of looks like someone might call something like\n\n  while (encodeRows(\u003csome value\u003e)\n\nBut then they don\u0027t need to use a loop, since they can just pass the height (or some really large number).\n\nIf the client passes \u003c\u003d 0, maybe that should be a signal to encode all lines remaining?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 56,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "3adbc4e8f7ccf31da575ae74f11df7f4e89fd46e",
